<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="128.[151,1437,386,2030]" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis box="[151,273,386,411]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,386,411]" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
A white frons with an irroration of dark, ochreous- tipped scales, transverse fasciae of more or less equal width on costal and dorsal margins of forewing make this species easily distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Prins" authorityYear="2012" box="[1264,1399,423,446]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Phyllonorycter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rongensis">
<emphasis box="[1264,1399,423,446]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">P. rongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In females, the anterior apophyses are ca. 2/3 as long as posterior apophyses in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vari" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1013,1157,459,483]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Phyllonorycter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melhaniae">
<emphasis box="[1013,1157,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">P. melhaniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Prins" authorityYear="2012" box="[1300,1436,459,482]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Phyllonorycter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rongensis">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,459,482]" italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">P. rongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
anterior apophyses are only slightly shorter than posterior apophyses.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
